rComments: He is incomprehensible because of his strong accent. I can't understand him at all. but this class covers several interesting topics with long readings. the tests are 2 hrs long and done online. three map quizzes and two essays. they aren't so bad. also, some test questions came out from the readings so make sure you glance thru them.

The class itself is very easy. The points are very generously spread, with simple participation points counting for alot aka just showing up. Its hard to understand what he says at times and his lectures can be a little confusing, but overall good easy class. There is a decent amount of reading but its pretty much optional.
Incomprehensible lectures with long overly dramatic pauses. Speaks quietly in a massive auditorium. Subjects in class are nearly always boring, random, or useless.
Ashwini has interesting stories, but the material in the class is a little dry. You only have to go to lecture once every two weeks, for map quizzes. Otherwise everything else is online.
Excellent teacher, very interesting topic. Not like your every day classes. Emphasis on actually learning the material and appreciating it, instead of just testing how well you memorize.

Before taking this class, I heard it was the easiest class on campus. I beg to differ. The lectures are boring, but posted online. The tests are online as well and you have plenty of time to take them. But, the number of readings is ridiculous for a 100 level class. If you love reading about Africa's poverty, take this class.
Very easy class, exams are online with a 2 hour time limit, which is more than enough time to look up anything you don't know. Not very interesting lectures though...
Very boring. Mostly incomprehensible. Speech is riddled with long pauses. I always fell asleep in class even though I loved the subject.
